In mathematics, Arnold's cat map is a chaotic map from the torus into itself, named after Vladimir Arnold, who demonstrated its effects in the 1960s using an image of a cat, hence the name.Thinking of the torus 
  
    
      
        
          
            T
          
          
            2
          
        
      
    
